TITLE: State Management Hook
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet presents a state management hook, `useCounter`, which manages a counter value and provides an increment function. It uses `useState` to hold the counter value and `useCallback` to memoize the increment function, preventing unnecessary re-renders. The hook returns the current count and the increment function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sendarcade/solana-app-kit/blob/main/src/shared/hooks/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const useCounter = (initialValue = 0) => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(initialValue);

  const increment = useCallback(() => {
    setCount(prev => prev + 1);
  }, []);

  return { count, increment };
};
```

