TITLE: Testing React Hook
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to test a React hook using `@testing-library/react-hooks`. It uses `renderHook` to render the hook and `act` to simulate asynchronous actions, ensuring that state transitions are properly handled.  The example tests the `useAuth` hook and verifies that the `user` state is defined after a successful login.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sendarcade/solana-app-kit/blob/main/src/shared/hooks/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { renderHook, act } from '@testing-library/react-hooks';

describe('useAuth', () => {
  it('should handle login', async () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useAuth());

    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.login(mockCredentials);
    });

    expect(result.current.user).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```

